# Clean the joelclaw working tree and deploy Telegram auditing

## Goal

Preserve all intentional work in the dirty Flagg checkout, remove generated junk, group changes into logical commits, reconcile the 181 local-only commits with 9 remote-only commits, push safely, deploy the Telegram audit slice, and prove the live path.

## Result

- Backed up original HEAD `c1cf7e36cd55194eefd4121e87767b409b62b47f` to remote branch `backup/flagg-pre-clean-20260715-0915`.
- Saved tracked and untracked recovery artifacts under `~/.local/state/joelclaw-cleanup-backups/20260715-0915-*` with SHA-256 receipts.
- Rebasing 181 local-only commits onto the 9 remote commits completed with zero conflicts.
- Moved 239 `.pi-subagents` artifacts, Python bytecode, and the accidental `pipe` file outside the repo into the cleanup backup directory.
- Moved nine misplaced `./~/.rhizomatic/outbox/*.json` records into the real `~/.rhizomatic/outbox/` instead of deleting queued state.
- Added ignore rules for `.pi-subagents`, Python bytecode, `/pipe`, and `/~/`.
- Captured all intentional dirty work in twelve ShitRat-authored logical commits, then pushed the reconciled 193-commit fast-forward to `origin/main` without force.
- Added a final ShitRat commit fixing ClickHouse CLI config resolution: `ca1badedf6961d6a353381a5d84b2571c9b31638`.
- Working tree and `origin/main` are aligned and clean.

## Logical commits

- `b5f7da86` chore(repo): ignore generated runtime debris
- `48c8506c` fix(fleet): probe the local host without SSH
- `6627caa6` test(voice): verify call telemetry mutations
- `9360edf6` fix(content): point custody paths at joelclaw-api
- `4e8575e3` fix(gateway): restore Slack socket lifecycle module
